FINANCIAL FEATURE ENGINEERING

Why: To make the model specifically for financial sector detection

14 Features Engineered:

1. url_length           → Length of URL (phishing URLs often longer)
2. has_https            → Uses HTTPS? (legitimate sites almost always do)
3. has_ip_address       → Uses IP instead of domain? (highly suspicious)
4. digit_count          → Number of digits (phishing uses numbers to hide)
5. hyphen_count         → Number of hyphens (common in fake domains)
6. subdomain_count      → Number of subdomains (excessive = suspicious)
7. domain_length        → Length of domain name
8. financial_keywords   → Count of: login, verify, account, etc.
9. bank_keywords        → Count of: chase, paypal, visa, etc.
10. urgency_keywords    → Count of: urgent, suspended, verify now, etc.
11. suspicious_tld      → TLD in {.xyz, .top, .click, etc.}
12. has_at_symbol       → Contains @? (classic phishing trick)
13. has_double_slash    → Unusual // pattern?
14. url_entropy         → Randomness score (high = algorithmically generated)

Financial Keyword Lists:
- Financial: login, signin, verify, secure, account, banking, transfer, etc.
- Bank: chase, paypal, visa, mastercard, bankofamerica, wells fargo, etc.
- Urgency: urgent, suspend, suspended, limited, expire, alert, etc.
- Suspicious TLDs: .xyz, .top, .click, .link, .win, .gq, .ml, .cf, etc.
